  <section id="launch_install_cd">
    <title>Get and launch the installation CD</title>

    <para>
      If you haven't an Ulteo OVD DVD-ROM yet, please donwload the corresponding ISO file from
      <ulink url="http://www.ulteo.com/main/downloads/ulteo-ovd-iso.php?suite=3.0">this place at www.ulteo.com</ulink> and burn it to a fresh DVD.
    </para>

    <para>
      Insert the Ulteo OVD DVD-ROM into your computer and restart it.
      If you selected the DVD-ROM as first boot device you'll see the
      bootloader following interface:
    </para>

    <itemizedlist>

      <listitem>
        <para>Choose a language:</para>
        <para><screenshot>
          <screeninfo>DVDrom GFXBoot1</screeninfo>
          <graphic fileref="img/iso/gfxboot1.png"/>
        </screenshot></para>
        <beginpage />
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para>Select <emphasis>Install Ulteo</emphasis></para>
        <para><screenshot>
          <screeninfo>DVDrom GFXBoot2</screeninfo>
          <graphic fileref="img/iso/gfxboot2.png"/>
        </screenshot></para>
        <beginpage />
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para>The system is now going to boot. It may take some time.</para>
        <para><screenshot>
        <screeninfo>Live CD boot splash screen</screeninfo>
          <anchor id="splash_screen" />
          <graphic fileref="img/iso/splash_livecd.png"/>
        </screenshot></para>
        <beginpage />
      </listitem>

    </itemizedlist>

  </section>

  <section id="install">
    <title>Installation</title>

    <itemizedlist>

      <listitem>
        <para>
          The first step is used to select the system language. Choose your language from the list 
          and click on <emphasis>Forward</emphasis>.
        </para>
        <para><screenshot>
          <screeninfo>ubiquity - step 1 - language</screeninfo>
          <graphic fileref="img/iso/ubiquity_language.png"></graphic>
        </screenshot></para>
        <beginpage />
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para>
          In the second step, the system asks you to define your
          location. Either select a point on the map or choose one from
          the <emphasis>Selected city</emphasis> form and click on
          <emphasis>Forward</emphasis>.
        </para>
        <para><screenshot>
          <screeninfo>ubiquity - step 2 - timezone</screeninfo>
          <graphic fileref="img/iso/ubiquity_timezone.png"></graphic>
        </screenshot></para>
        <beginpage />
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para>
          The third step is used to define the keyboard layout. Select
          yours and click on <emphasis>Forward</emphasis>.
        </para>
        <para><screenshot>
          <screeninfo>ubiquity - step 3 - keyboard layout</screeninfo>
          <graphic fileref="img/iso/ubiquity_keyboard_layout.png"></graphic>
        </screenshot></para>
        <beginpage />
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para>
          Then, you have to select the partitioning method. We suggest
          the automatic method: <emphasis>Erase and use the entire
          disk</emphasis>.
        </para>
        <para><screenshot>
          <screeninfo>ubiquity - step 4 - partman</screeninfo>
          <graphic fileref="img/iso/ubiquity_partman.png"></graphic>
        </screenshot></para>
        <beginpage />
      </listitem>


      <listitem>
        <anchor id="identity_info" />
        <para>
          These questions are about the installed operating system
          itself, user login and password used to access the OS, along
          with the hostname of the machine.
        </para>
        <para><screenshot>
          <screeninfo>ubiquity - step 6 - identity information</screeninfo>
          <graphic fileref="img/iso/ubiquity_identity_info.png"></graphic>
        </screenshot></para>
        <beginpage />
      </listitem>

     <listitem>
        <anchor id="ovd_configuration" />
        <para>
          Type a password and confirm it.
          Useful address is displayed to you for a near future use of OVD.
        </para>
        <para><screenshot>
          <screeninfo>ubiquity - step 7 - OVD configuration</screeninfo>
          <graphic fileref="img/iso/ubiquity_ovd_configuration.png"></graphic>
        </screenshot></para>
        <beginpage />
     </listitem>

     <listitem>
        <para>
          Now read carefully the installation summary, then
          click on <emphasis>Install</emphasis>.
        </para>
        <para><screenshot>
  	      <screeninfo>ubiquity - step 8 - summary</screeninfo>
          <graphic fileref="img/iso/ubiquity_summary.png"></graphic>
        </screenshot></para>
        <beginpage />
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
      <para> Now, you just have to wait during the system installation. </para>
        <para><screenshot>
          <screeninfo>ubiquity - install OVD system</screeninfo>
          <graphic fileref="img/iso/ubiquity_install_system.png"></graphic>
        </screenshot></para>
        <beginpage />
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para> Finally, click on <emphasis>Restart now</emphasis>.  </para>
        <para><screenshot>
          <screeninfo>ubiquity - restart</screeninfo>
          <graphic fileref="img/iso/ubiquity_restart.png"></graphic>
        </screenshot></para>
        <beginpage />
      </listitem>

    </itemizedlist>
  </section>

  <section id="system_boot">
    <title>First boot</title>
    <para>
      Wait that the new OVD system has rebooted. It displays again the same
      <ulink url="#splash_screen">boot splash screen</ulink> as seen before.
    </para>
    <para>
      Once the OVD has rebooted, it shows up the login prompt system and waits.
      Useful OVD URL information is recalled to you.
    </para>
    <para><screenshot>
      <screeninfo>OVD system - first boot</screeninfo>
      <graphic fileref="img/iso/system_prompt.png"></graphic>
    </screenshot></para>
    <para>
      Logging in to the OVD system is recommended to experimented users. Login id and password are
      the same as used during the <ulink url="#identity_info">fifth step</ulink> of installation.
    </para>
  </section>

  <section id="configuration">
    <title>Configure your Application Server</title>

    <para>
      Once you can access the Ulteo system from your browser, go
      to the administration console:
      <ulink url="http://10.42.1.242/ovd/admin" /> and authenticate yourself.
    </para>

      <para>
        The administrator login and password are both those filled at the
        <ulink url="#ovd_configuration" >sixth step</ulink> of installation.
      </para>

    <para>
      <inlinemediaobject>
      <imageobject>
        <imagedata fileref="img/sm_www_admin_login.png"/>
      </imageobject>
      <textobject>
        <phrase>Session Manager admin login</phrase>
      </textobject>
      </inlinemediaobject>
    </para>

    <para>
      Then you arrive at the main administrator menu in the Web interface.
    </para>

    <para>
      <inlinemediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata fileref="img/sm_admin_main.png"/>
        </imageobject>
        <textobject>
          <phrase>Session Manager admin main page</phrase>
        </textobject>
      </inlinemediaobject>
    </para>

    <para>
      To administrate the OVD, follow the corresponding online
      <ulink url="http://doc.ulteo.com/3.0/AdminConsole.html" >documentation</ulink>.
    </para>

  </section>

